Actress Victoria Kolawole aka chacha has taken to social media to express frustration over the biting fuel scarcity. The movie writer revealed a supposed innocent-looking fan, who approached her and promised to help get fuel, has fled with her keg and money. According to her, even though she tipped the young some extra cash, he refused to show up with the most important item in her life currently. Read Also: I’ll marry any man that sends me fuel-Waje   I’ll marry any man that sends me fuel-Waje     It is my choice to be a second wife, Mercy Aigbe tells…     2022 Headies: I deserve an award, says Portable ‘Zazu’   Narrating her sad encounter, she wrote: “So I went to the filling station today but too much queue so, I couldn’t come down from the car. “Luckily for me, I saw this innocent looking guy, he came to me and said he’s my fan. He promised to help me get the fuel. “So, I gave him money and my keg, still give him extra money. Till now I no see the guy or the fuel. Emphasizing her current condition, Kolawole added: “I NEED FUEL, I’M FRUSTRATED.”